WEBVTT

00:05.005 --> 00:05.973 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:06.006 --> 00:06.974 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.007 --> 00:08.876 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And I'm Gwen Ifill.

00:08.909 --> 00:11.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We bring you the
"NewsHour"
tonight from the Wells Fargo
Center in Philadelphia,

00:11.678 --> 00:14.915 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
site of this week's Democratic
National Convention.

00:14.948 --> 00:17.184 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: It's day two here.

00:17.217 --> 00:22.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Delegates are set to make
history by nominating
a woman for the first time to
top a major

00:22.789 --> 00:24.625 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
party's presidential ticket.

00:24.658 --> 00:29.763 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And with
President Bill Clinton
speaking tonight, we look back
at a different

00:29.796 --> 00:36.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
kind of first lady, in part two
of our Hillary
biography series: the ups and
downs of her

00:36.470 --> 00:38.205 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
eight years in the White House.

00:38.238 --> 00:40.574 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID GERGEN, Former White House
Aide: She
knows the issues better than
anybody I know,

00:40.607 --> 00:42.142 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
including her husband.

00:42.175 --> 00:45.712 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That was threatening to some
people, to some
voters.

00:45.746 --> 00:47.581 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And I'm Hari
Sreenivasan
in Washington.

00:47.614 --> 00:52.185 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We will have all the
non-convention news of
the day, including polluted
water, corruption,

00:52.219 --> 00:56.456 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and a crumbling economy -- why
Venezuela's
oil problem is crippling the
country.

00:56.490 --> 00:59.359 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSE GREGORIO GARCIA, Fisherman
(through translator):
The oil goes to the bottom of
the lake.

00:59.393 --> 01:01.128 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's where the crab is.

01:01.161 --> 01:03.764 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It migrates, or dies, or gets
covered with
petroleum, and when it's stained
like that,

01:03.797 --> 01:05.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
no one will buy it.

01:05.999 --> 01:14.374 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: All that and more on
tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:14.408 --> 01:17.311 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:17.344 --> 01:27.654 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Hillary Clinton once
called it
the highest, hardest glass
ceiling, the barrier

01:27.688 --> 01:30.891 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to a woman becoming president of
the United
States.

01:30.924 --> 01:35.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tonight, she's being named the
Democratic
presidential nominee, after
turning away a

01:35.362 --> 01:40.434 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
vigorous primary challenge from
Bernie Sanders
that extended this week onto the
streets of

01:40.467 --> 01:42.803 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Philadelphia and the floor of
the convention.

01:42.836 --> 01:46.807 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In fact, behind us now, the
delegates have
begun to cast their votes.

01:46.840 --> 01:51.611 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We will come back to that a
little later,
but, first, correspondent Lisa
Desjardins

01:51.645 --> 01:53.113 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
begins our coverage.

01:53.146 --> 01:54.581 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MAN: Bernie Sanders!

01:54.614 --> 01:56.350 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

01:56.383 --> 02:00.787 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: This is Hillary
Clinton's
nomination night, but Bernie
Sanders still

02:00.821 --> 02:05.859 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
got a standing ovation from New
York delegates
this morning as he pushed again
for uniting

02:05.892 --> 02:06.927 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
against Donald Trump.

02:06.960 --> 02:08.762 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

02:08.795 --> 02:12.099 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
BERNIE SANDERS (VT-I),
Presidential Candidate:
We must defeat the worst
Republican candidate

02:12.132 --> 02:14.434 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in modern history of this
country.

02:14.468 --> 02:15.635 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

02:15.669 --> 02:18.205 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But it's not
all unity yet.

02:18.238 --> 02:23.377 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A Sanders backer touched off a
shouting match
at a Texas delegation breakfast.

02:23.410 --> 02:24.945 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAN: We want to be clear.

02:24.978 --> 02:31.585 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We are currently condemning our
current presumptive
nominee.

02:31.618 --> 02:32.819 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BOOING)

02:32.853 --> 02:35.889 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAN: You folks need to grow up.

02:35.922 --> 02:38.592 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You need to grow up.

02:38.625 --> 02:41.328 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WOMAN: Get out of here.

02:41.361 --> 02:43.130 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
She won.

02:43.163 --> 02:46.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Vice President
Biden played
down the divisions as he walked
through the

02:46.566 --> 02:51.204 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
convention floor, chatting with
delegates
and saying that he thinks
Sanders supporters

02:51.238 --> 02:53.440 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
will rally behind Clinton in the
end.

02:53.473 --> 02:55.609 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSEPH BIDEN, Vice President of
the United
States: We have to be a little
graceful here.

02:55.642 --> 03:00.914 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, the senator, the
delegates worked
their tail off.

03:00.947 --> 03:03.784 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And they're here in large
numbers.

03:03.817 --> 03:05.819 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They get a chance, man.

03:05.852 --> 03:07.421 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Give them a chance.

03:07.454 --> 03:09.456 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I promise you they're going to
be fine.

03:09.489 --> 03:14.027 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: After this
evening's state-by-state
roll call vote, the focus shifts
to Hillary

03:14.061 --> 03:18.331 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Clinton's experience, and the
delegates hear
from top Democrats, past and
present.

03:18.365 --> 03:22.903 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Democratic women of the U.S.
House, led
by Minority Leader Nancy Pelosi,
will take

03:22.936 --> 03:24.638 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the stage early.

03:24.671 --> 03:29.176 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Former Attorney General Eric
Holder will speak
to Clinton's stand on social
justice.

03:29.209 --> 03:35.415 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And former President Bill
Clinton will round
out the night, making the case
for his wife.

03:35.449 --> 03:40.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Republican Donald Trump had a
decidedly different
take at the Veterans of Foreign
Wars Convention

03:40.087 --> 03:42.022 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in Charlotte, North Carolina.

03:42.055 --> 03:46.827 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He roundly criticized Clinton
and the Democrats
gathered in Philadelphia for
making no mention

03:46.860 --> 03:49.763 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the Islamic State or threat
of terrorism
so far.

03:49.796 --> 03:54.334 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), Presidential
Candidate:
We need to change our foreign
policy to focus

03:54.367 --> 04:00.574 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on defeating and destroying
ISIS, a word you
didn't hear last night at the
Democrat Convention.

04:00.607 --> 04:02.375 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You didn't hear about it.

04:02.409 --> 04:09.683 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They don't want to talk about
it, because
in a very true way they really
established

04:09.716 --> 04:11.485 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ISIS because of weakness.

04:11.518 --> 04:16.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Meanwhile, at
an economic
summit in Laos, Secretary of
State John Kerry

04:16.389 --> 04:21.161 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
raised Moscow's alleged
involvement in hacking
the Democratic National
Committee's e-mails.

04:21.194 --> 04:25.332 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But Russian Foreign Minister
Sergei Lavrov
dismissed the issue.

04:25.365 --> 04:29.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
QUESTION: What do you say of
U.S. accusations
that Russia hacked the
Democratic Party's

04:29.469 --> 04:31.171 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
e-mails?

04:31.204 --> 04:34.674 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SERGEI LAVROV, Russian Foreign
Minister: Well,
I don't want to use four-letter
words.

04:34.708 --> 04:39.045 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The Clinton
campaign said
today there's no evidence that
its e-mail

04:39.079 --> 04:40.547 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
system has been breached.

04:40.580 --> 04:44.317 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm Lisa
Desjardins.

04:44.351 --> 04:50.290 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Next, we head
down to the convention
floor, where NPR's "Weekend
Edition Sunday"

04:50.323 --> 04:52.159 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
host Rachel Martin is standing
by.

04:52.192 --> 04:57.664 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Rachel is joining us every night
this week
as part of our joint "PBS
NewsHour"/NPR convention

04:57.697 --> 04:58.798 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
coverage.

04:58.832 --> 04:59.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, Rachel, what should are you
looking for
tonight?

04:59.900 --> 05:01.768 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
RACHEL MARTIN: Hi, Judy.

05:01.801 --> 05:06.506 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, yes, as you can hear
behind me, the
roll call is still going on,
and, as was mentioned

05:06.540 --> 05:10.810 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in that piece that just preceded
me, history
is happening here tonight.

05:10.844 --> 05:15.415 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the Democratic Party is
hoping that history
can help heal the divisions that
still exist

05:15.448 --> 05:19.953 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
between Bernie Sanders
supporters and those
in this arena who are supporting
Hillary Clinton.

05:19.986 --> 05:24.424 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There will be a whole slew of
speaks on this
stage tonight who will be making
the case

05:24.457 --> 05:26.293 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for Hillary Clinton.

05:26.326 --> 05:31.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The theme of the campaign
tonight is supposed
to focus on Hillary Clinton's
experience,

05:31.498 --> 05:34.668 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
sticking up for children and
families over
her career.

05:34.701 --> 05:38.838 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To that end, we're going to hear
from the
so-called mothers of the
movement.

05:38.872 --> 05:43.877 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
These are the mothers of Eric
Garner, Trayvon
Martin, Sandra Bland and others,
who will

05:43.910 --> 05:49.049 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be addressing the issue of
police brutality
in this country, race relations.

05:49.082 --> 05:54.921 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We will also be hearing an
important speech
tonight from former President
Bill Clinton.

05:54.955 --> 06:00.126 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
By our count, it will be the
eighth time that
President Clinton has addressed
the Democratic

06:00.160 --> 06:01.861 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
National Convention.

06:01.895 --> 06:07.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This will be, perhaps, the most
important
speech he has ever given in this
arena, as

06:07.100 --> 06:13.006 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
he endorses his own wife for
president of
the United States -- back to
you, Judy and

06:13.039 --> 06:14.007 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Gwen.

06:14.040 --> 06:15.008 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Making history,
Rachel.

06:15.041 --> 06:16.142 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We will be glued to all of it.

06:16.176 --> 06:17.143 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Thanks.

06:17.177 --> 06:19.012 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Thank you, Rachel.

06:19.045 --> 06:23.750 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Our next guest shattered her own
glass ceiling
in 2007, when she was elected
the first woman

06:23.783 --> 06:26.152 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
speaker of the House of
Representatives.

06:26.186 --> 06:29.155 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now Minority Leader Nancy Pelosi
joins us
now.

06:29.189 --> 06:30.156 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Welcome.

06:30.190 --> 06:31.324 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

06:31.358 --> 06:33.059 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NANCY PELOSI (D-CA), House
Minority Leader:
Pleasure.

06:33.093 --> 06:34.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: It's so good to see
you here,
but I'm wondering, as you watch
this roll

06:35.028 --> 06:41.768 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
call play out, where the Bernie
Sanders supporters
are still getting their final
cry in, whether

06:41.801 --> 06:44.204 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you think that you're signaling
unity with
this.

06:44.237 --> 06:45.205 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

06:45.238 --> 06:47.841 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NANCY PELOSI: We're signaling
strength.

06:47.874 --> 06:52.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As we disagree with each other,
we learn more
about each other, and more and
more people

06:52.379 --> 06:53.747 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
are coming together.

06:53.780 --> 06:55.548 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Some may never get there.

06:55.582 --> 06:57.917 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They just may not get there.

06:57.951 --> 07:01.655 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But, largely, this convention is
coming together.

07:01.688 --> 07:07.494 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Everybody understands that,
whatever our differences,
they're vastly small compared to
the vast

07:07.527 --> 07:11.431 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
difference between the Democrats
and the Republicans,
between Hillary Clinton and the
Republican

07:11.464 --> 07:12.799 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
nominee.

07:12.832 --> 07:16.503 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I'm curious about
your own
delegation, Madam Leader.

07:16.536 --> 07:21.441 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
California, 300-some delegates
for Hillary
Clinton, but over 200 delegates
for Bernie

07:21.474 --> 07:25.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sanders, how is the California
-- they're
the best, the biggest, most
populous state

07:25.578 --> 07:26.546 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in the country.

07:26.579 --> 07:27.580 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How are they coming together?

07:27.614 --> 07:28.581 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

07:28.615 --> 07:30.116 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NANCY PELOSI: They will come
together.

07:30.150 --> 07:31.918 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We will have the biggest vote in
the country,
of course, for Hillary Clinton.

07:31.951 --> 07:37.057 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Our Governor Brown just said
that he thinks
we can win by 20 points for
Hillary Clinton

07:37.090 --> 07:38.058 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in California.

07:38.091 --> 07:39.059 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We will see.

07:39.092 --> 07:40.860 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But it's going to be big.

07:40.894 --> 07:45.465 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: So, Donald Trump is,
what, making
things up when he says he's
going to compete

07:45.498 --> 07:46.466 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in California?

07:46.499 --> 07:47.467 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

07:47.500 --> 07:48.468 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NANCY PELOSI: Let him think
that.

07:48.501 --> 07:49.536 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

07:49.569 --> 07:50.970 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: OK, let me ask you,
how you do
win?

07:51.004 --> 07:54.574 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What is key going forward,
leaving Philadelphia,
for your nominee?

07:54.607 --> 07:56.376 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

07:56.409 --> 07:58.745 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NANCY PELOSI: Well, what is key
for winning
the election is to be able to
put forth a

07:58.778 --> 08:05.118 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
vision for our future and how
this election
affects people's lives.

08:05.151 --> 08:10.156 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We're about rejecting
trickle-down economics,
instead an economy that works
for everyone,

08:10.190 --> 08:11.825 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
not just the privileged few.

08:11.858 --> 08:16.429 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In terms of winning the
election, it's all
about turnout and how we connect
with the

08:16.463 --> 08:23.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
voter as to what it means in
their lives to
turn out to vote, to win the
House, the Senate,

08:23.470 --> 08:26.973 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
statehouses, state governorships
and the rest.

08:27.006 --> 08:28.308 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, turnout is everything.

08:28.341 --> 08:33.279 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And turnout really runs on the
fuel of inspiration.

08:33.313 --> 08:39.919 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I believe Hillary Clinton's
vision, based
on her experience, based on her
knowledge

08:39.953 --> 08:45.492 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and judgment, as well as her
connection with
the American people, after a
lifetime of service

08:45.525 --> 08:48.461 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and leadership for America's
families and
children.

08:48.495 --> 08:52.399 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I don't think
anyone is closer
to the voters in Washington than
members of

08:52.432 --> 08:53.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the House of Representatives.

