36:30.422 --> 36:35.393 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
NADJA DROST: In order to
traverse this frontier
land with their contraband
goods, smugglers

36:35.427 --> 36:40.031 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have to pay off everyone, from
authorities
to rebels and other armed groups
from the

36:40.065 --> 36:41.966 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Colombian side.

36:42.000 --> 36:46.104 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): You
pay the military,
the national guard, the police,
the intelligence

36:46.137 --> 36:47.505 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
agency, military intelligence.

36:47.539 --> 36:50.275 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You even pay the Colombian
guerrillas.

36:50.308 --> 36:51.409 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Everyone eats from this.

36:51.443 --> 36:52.911 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
NADJA DROST: Colombian
paramilitaries, too,
he says.

36:52.944 --> 36:58.149 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN (through translator): If you
don't pay,
you will get shot, at the least.

36:58.183 --> 37:02.954 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: We arrive at a
lake, where workers
line up empty barrels to tow
across, where

37:02.987 --> 37:07.625 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they will get filled at a
rudimentary gas
station, loaded onto trucks and
continue their

37:07.659 --> 37:10.228 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
journey to the other side of the
border.

37:10.261 --> 37:15.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Many people live off this trade,
including
the military's national guard,
who we see

37:15.233 --> 37:20.805 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
inspecting every vehicle, except
for trucks
with contraband gasoline, at a
checkpoint

37:20.839 --> 37:24.542 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a mere 10 miles before a closed
border crossing.

37:24.576 --> 37:29.914 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As we peer out from behind our
tinted windows,
a local accompanying us explains
how contraband

37:29.948 --> 37:31.149 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
gets across here.

37:31.182 --> 37:33.351 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN (through translator): Those
civilians
are the moscas.

37:33.384 --> 37:38.890 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: Moscas, flies, the
name given
to civilians buzzing around on
motorbikes

37:38.923 --> 37:43.328 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who act as a link between
smugglers and whichever
group they have to pay off.

37:43.361 --> 37:45.363 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Here, it's the military.

37:45.396 --> 37:49.934 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): One of
them already
arranged everything and paid the
military,

37:49.968 --> 37:51.903 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
so that these trucks can pass
through.

37:51.936 --> 37:58.309 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: Truckload after
truckload, contraband
gasoline is waved on through by
the military.

37:58.343 --> 38:00.945 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Smuggling rackets keep draining
oil profits.

38:00.979 --> 38:03.748 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Oil wells in Lake Maracaibo
continue to decline.

38:03.781 --> 38:09.754 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As the oil economy tumbles, and
pulls Venezuela
deeper into crisis, it draws
attention to

38:09.787 --> 38:14.392 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the perils of over-relying on
oil revenues
to prop up an economy.

38:14.425 --> 38:22.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Back on Lake Maracaibo,
fisherman Jose Gregorio
Garcia has benefited from oil's
bonanza years,

38:22.167 --> 38:27.172 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as well as suffered from too
much oil, contaminating
his fish supply.

38:27.205 --> 38:32.210 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Living shoreside of the
once-booming oil industry,
Garcia knows it has to change.

38:32.243 --> 38:36.581 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSE GREGORIO GARCIA (through
translator):
We have seen what happens with
petroleum.

38:36.614 --> 38:38.883 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The price of oil rises, and it
falls.

38:38.917 --> 38:41.719 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have always lived off this,
the good price
of oil.

38:41.753 --> 38:43.621 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But we have to find an
alternative.

38:43.655 --> 38:48.359 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NADJA DROST: For the "PBS
NewsHour," reporting
with Bruno Federico, I'm Nadja
Drost on Lake

38:48.393 --> 38:50.128 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Maracaibo.

38:50.161 --> 38:53.431 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: To hear more
about this
story and our reporting from
Venezuela, check

38:53.464 --> 38:57.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
out our Outside the Bubble
conversation with
special correspondent Nadja
Drost.

38:57.335 --> 39:00.738 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's on our Facebook page,
Facebook.com/NewsHour.

39:00.772 --> 39:04.042 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now we go back to Gwen and Judy
in Philadelphia.

39:04.075 --> 39:07.845 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Thank you, Hari.

39:07.879 --> 39:12.483 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We are here at the convention
hall in Philadelphia,
as the roll call continues.

39:12.517 --> 39:18.790 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
South Dakota has just put
Hillary Clinton
over the top, meaning that she
has won more

39:18.823 --> 39:24.295 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
than the 2,382 delegate votes
she needed to
wrap up the nomination.

39:24.329 --> 39:30.301 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What started as a Twitter
hashtag in 2013
after the acquittal of George
Zimmerman for

39:30.335 --> 39:38.276 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the murder of Trayvon Martin has
grown into
an activist protest
organization, with increasing

39:38.309 --> 39:39.477 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
influence.

39:39.510 --> 39:41.379 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
John Yang has our report.

39:41.412 --> 39:49.287 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Less than 10 miles
from the Democratic
Convention, demonstrators remind
delegates,

39:49.320 --> 39:50.588 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
black lives matter.

39:50.622 --> 39:52.890 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
WOMAN: They need to pay
attention to the will
of the people.

39:52.924 --> 39:56.027 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: We need a radical new
system, because
the one we have is broken, and
it's not working

39:56.060 --> 39:57.795 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for any of us here in America.

39:57.829 --> 40:02.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: The issue of race
relations looms
over this presidential campaign,
driven by

40:02.400 --> 40:08.406 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the high-profile deaths of black
men and women
at the hands of police, which
triggered demonstrations

40:08.439 --> 40:10.608 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
like this one.

40:10.642 --> 40:14.846 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Just last week, Hillary Clinton
stressed her
commitment to the
African-American community

40:14.879 --> 40:17.282 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
after police shootings in
Louisiana and Minnesota.

40:17.315 --> 40:21.219 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HILLARY RODHAM CLINTON (D),
Presidential Candidate:
We white Americans need to do a
better job

40:21.252 --> 40:28.860 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
of listening when
African-Americans talk about
the seen and unseen barriers you
face every

40:28.893 --> 40:30.628 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
day.

40:30.662 --> 40:34.265 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: During the primaries,
Black Lives
Matter protesters confronted
both Clinton

40:34.299 --> 40:38.303 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and her rival, Vermont Senator
Bernie Sanders.

40:38.336 --> 40:40.638 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Representative Barbara Lee
understands their
demands.

40:40.672 --> 40:42.407 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

40:42.440 --> 40:43.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARBARA LEE (D), California:
Young people
involved in the Black Lives
Matter movement,

40:43.975 --> 40:48.079 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
they're holding us all
accountable to an agenda
to make this country better.

40:48.112 --> 40:51.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Shaun Harper is
director of the
Center for the Study of Race and
Equity in

40:51.783 --> 40:53.751 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Education at the University of
Pennsylvania.

40:53.785 --> 40:55.553 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SHAUN HARPER, Executive
Director, Center for
the Study of Race and Equity in
Education,

40:55.586 --> 40:58.423 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
University of Pennsylvania: I
think that,
from that moment onward, that
both Senator

40:58.456 --> 41:05.063 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sanders and Secretary Clinton
understood this
is a movement to be taken
seriously.

41:05.096 --> 41:09.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Retaliation against
the police
has created a tension between
supporting the

41:09.434 --> 41:13.171 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
victims of police shootings and
supporting
law enforcement.

41:13.204 --> 41:16.741 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm John
Yang in Philadelphia.

41:16.774 --> 41:23.348 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Jordan Davis was 17
years old
when he was shot and killed in
2012.

41:23.381 --> 41:27.885 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
His assailant claimed Davis and
his friends
were playing their music too
loud.

41:27.919 --> 41:32.357 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
His mother, Lucia McBath, and
six other mothers
who have lost children to gun
violence will

41:32.390 --> 41:36.160 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
appear together on the
convention stage tonight.

41:36.194 --> 41:38.463 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We spoke with her a short time
ago.

41:38.496 --> 41:41.432 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lucia McBath, thank you so much
for joining
us.

41:41.466 --> 41:42.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LUCIA MCBATH, Mother of Shooting
Victim: Thank
you for having me.

41:42.467 --> 41:43.701 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Talk about your son.

41:43.735 --> 41:45.636 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And talk about your reason for
being on the
stage tonight.

41:45.670 --> 41:51.109 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have been -- our country has
been so caught
up in a discussion about law
enforcement vs.

41:51.142 --> 41:52.944 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
police abuse.

41:52.977 --> 41:56.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And even though your son wasn't
a victim,
wasn't quite in that mix, what
-- how have

41:56.881 --> 41:58.216 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
you been watching this unfold?

41:58.249 --> 42:01.686 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LUCIA MCBATH: Oh, well, it's
been disheartening,
of course.

42:01.719 --> 42:07.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And what we're beginning to
recognize is that,
you know, gun violence is in
many, many forms,

42:07.825 --> 42:13.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you know, whether it's law
enforcement on
individual citizens, or if it's
individual

42:13.197 --> 42:17.902 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
citizens that are gunning down
law enforcement,
or if it's just, you know,
black-on-black

42:17.935 --> 42:18.870 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
crime.

42:18.903 --> 42:20.571 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It comes in all forms.

42:20.605 --> 42:25.243 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's very disheartening to
continue to
watch this evolve and erupt over
and over

42:25.276 --> 42:29.914 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and over again, because I know
firsthand,
as a victim of gun violence,
what this does,

42:29.947 --> 42:33.718 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not only to the victims, but to
the families
and their communities at large.

42:33.751 --> 42:37.221 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You have chosen
to endorse
Hillary Clinton.

42:37.255 --> 42:39.757 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You're here to support Hillary
Clinton.

42:39.791 --> 42:41.559 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
She's running for president.

42:41.592 --> 42:46.197 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So much of criminal justice,
though, occurs
-- these decisions occur at the
local level.

42:46.230 --> 42:47.698 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What difference can a president
make?

42:47.732 --> 42:51.436 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LUCIA MCBATH: Well, absolutely,
a president
has the heart of the people.

42:51.469 --> 42:53.771 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the president -- we follow
the lead of
the president.

42:53.805 --> 42:57.809 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If the president has a heart for
what's happening
in the nation, a heart for
people, wanting

42:57.842 --> 43:03.714 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to create and stimulate change
for the better,
preserving human life, then I
believe policy

43:03.748 --> 43:08.820 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
will fall right in under the
heels of the
changes that the president puts
in place for

43:08.853 --> 43:10.321 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the nation.

43:10.354 --> 43:11.923 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: You talk about the
-- what the
president can put in place.

43:11.956 --> 43:16.327 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You are also involved in my
Brother's Keeper
Initiative at the White House.

43:16.360 --> 43:20.965 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But I guess we who cover
Washington sometimes
see a lot of talk, and not a
whole lot of

43:20.998 --> 43:22.200 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
action.

43:22.233 --> 43:24.435 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I just wonder why you think
this might
be different.

43:24.469 --> 43:29.340 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LUCIA MCBATH: Well, I know this
will be different,
because I know Secretary Clinton
has been

43:29.373 --> 43:35.012 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
doing this work, championing for
human and
civil right within the
communities and the

43:35.046 --> 43:36.280 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
nation at large.

43:36.314 --> 43:38.783 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She's been doing this even
before she became
first lady.

43:38.816 --> 43:40.751 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She's been doing it as Senator
Clinton.

43:40.785 --> 43:42.720 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She's been doing it as secretary
of state.

43:42.753 --> 43:44.522 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So her record is firm.

43:44.555 --> 43:48.893 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it stands to reason that she
would continue
to serve and do what she's been
doing all

43:48.926 --> 43:49.894 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
along.

43:49.927 --> 43:51.028 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
So, I have hope.

43:51.062 --> 43:53.831 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I know that she has -- she's a
great visionary.

43:53.865 --> 43:58.970 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I understand that she really
is putting
in place some good measures,
solid measures

43:59.003 --> 44:01.272 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that will really be of the best
interests
of the nation.

44:01.305 --> 44:06.377 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Gwen mentioned
that this is
more than just about the role of
law enforcement,

44:06.410 --> 44:08.112 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
police.

44:08.145 --> 44:12.083 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Republican Convention, a big
part of their
message was they need to respect
the role

44:12.116 --> 44:13.951 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of police officers.

44:13.985 --> 44:19.123 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
How do you strike that balance
between saying
police need to not discriminate
when it comes

44:19.156 --> 44:23.895 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to dealing with black men and
women, but,
on the other hand, making sure
there's a respect

44:23.928 --> 44:25.596 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for the role of police?

44:25.630 --> 44:29.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LUCIA MCBATH: Well, I think it's
a matter
of retraining and reeducating on
both sides,

44:29.467 --> 44:33.571 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
citizens within the community
learning to
respect -- have a healthy
respect and regard

44:33.604 --> 44:35.973 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for police officers as our
protectors.

44:36.007 --> 44:42.480 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And at the same -- the same
measures, making
sure that our police are
reeducated, so that

44:42.513 --> 44:47.084 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they're able to understand
different cultures
and races and ethnicities.

44:47.118 --> 44:50.955 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And also, I think, too, that we
should have
police officers that actually
live within

44:50.988 --> 44:53.524 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
those various communities that
are serving
those individuals.

44:53.558 --> 44:59.430 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think that sets up a
better environment
for relation-building --
relationship-building,

44:59.463 --> 45:01.265 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
bridge-building.

45:01.299 --> 45:04.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think it's going to take a
lot of effort
within the community,
constituents within

45:04.335 --> 45:09.073 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the community, as well as the
police enforcement,
to really build those bridges.

45:09.106 --> 45:11.509 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's going to be a work on both
ends.

45:11.542 --> 45:13.978 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: We saw Michael
Jordan, the retired
basketball player, trying...

45:14.011 --> 45:15.846 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LUCIA MCBATH: Yes.

45:15.880 --> 45:17.248 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: ... to strike that
balance yesterday
with the million-dollar gift to
the NAACP

45:17.281 --> 45:20.685 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Legal Defense Fund and a
million-dollar gift
to the chiefs of police.

45:20.718 --> 45:22.219 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And it seems like that is the
middle ground.

45:22.253 --> 45:24.155 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LUCIA MCBATH: Absolutely.

45:24.188 --> 45:27.258 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: I want to end here
by asking you
to tell us a little bit about
your son, Jordan,

45:27.291 --> 45:30.261 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and what he would think about
you being such
a public figure now.

45:30.294 --> 45:33.898 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LUCIA MCBATH: Thank you for
giving me the
opportunity to talk about
Jordan, because

45:33.931 --> 45:37.435 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I just -- it helps me to keep
him alive.

45:37.468 --> 45:39.971 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Jordan was a child of inclusion.

